<paragraph id="D111B53FC369BA29FF18FCD180DCFB8D" blockId="21.[151,1436,838,1091]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
This combination was made by 
<bibRefCitation id="B53FC8CEC369BA29FD94FCD183E5FC48" author="Olivier, G. A." box="[539,761,876,902]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="85 - 100" refId="ref36628" refString="Olivier, G. A. (1791) Cochenille. Coccus. Genre d'insectes de la premiere section de l'ordre des Hemipteres. Pages 85 - 100, in: G. A. Olivier (editor), Encyclopedie methodique. Paris." type="book chapter" year="1791">Olivier (1791: 93)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="B53FC8CEC369BA29FC87FCD182E4FC48" author="Fernald, M. E." box="[776,1016,876,902]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref28767" refString="Fernald, M. E. (1903) A catalogue of the Coccidae of the world. Bulletin of the Hatch Experiment Station of the Massachusetts Agricultural College 88, 1 - 360." type="journal article" year="1903">Fernald (1903: 156)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously cited this trinomen as 
<taxonomicName id="16AECEBCC369BA29FF18FC2F8050FC65" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[151,332,914,939]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Coccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caricae">
<emphasis id="E3DA692DC369BA29FF18FC2F8050FC65" box="[151,332,914,939]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Coccus caricae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as did 
<bibRefCitation id="B53FC8CEC369BA29FE2FFC2F83EEFC62" author="Morrison, H. &amp; Renk, A. V." box="[416,754,914,940]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 222" refId="ref35937" refString="Morrison, H. &amp; Renk, A. V. (1957) A selected bibliography of the Coccoidea. Miscellaneous Publications United States Department of Agriculture 734, 1 - 222." type="journal article" year="1957">Morrison &amp; Renk (1957: 20)</bibRefCitation>
. Olivier quoted 
<bibRefCitation id="B53FC8CEC369BA29FC3EFC2F8579FC62" author="Bernard, J. E." box="[945,1125,914,940]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref24829" refString="Bernard, J. E. (1773) Quelle est la meilleure maniere de cultiver le figuier; quelles sont les causes de son deperissement, et quels sont les meilleurs moyens de remedier? Pages 1 - 124 in: Recueil des pieces presentees a l'Academie de Belles Lettres, Sciences et Arts de Marseille. Marseille: Francois Brebion." type="book chapter" year="1773">Bernard (1773)</bibRefCitation>
as the author, but 
<bibRefCitation id="B53FC8CEC369BA29FAB2FC2F8009FC1F" author="Bernard, J. E." pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 124" refId="ref24829" refString="Bernard, J. E. (1773) Quelle est la meilleure maniere de cultiver le figuier; quelles sont les causes de son deperissement, et quels sont les meilleurs moyens de remedier? Pages 1 - 124 in: Recueil des pieces presentees a l'Academie de Belles Lettres, Sciences et Arts de Marseille. Marseille: Francois Brebion." type="book chapter" year="1773">Bernard (1773: 89)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the vernacular name 
<taxonomicName id="16AECEBCC369BA29FD10FC0A83E6FC1F" box="[671,762,951,977]" class="Insecta" family="Kermesidae" genus="Kermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Kermes</taxonomicName>
du figuier. Olivier’s name was credited to Fabricius by 
<bibRefCitation id="B53FC8CEC369BA29FF18FC608325FC39" author="Boyer de Fonscolombe, E. L. J. H." box="[151,569,989,1015]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="201 - 218" refId="ref25610" refString="Boyer de Fonscolombe, E. L. J. H. (1834) Description des Kermes qu'on trouve aux environs d'Aix. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France 3, 201 - 218." type="journal article" year="1834">Boyer de Fonscolombe (1834: 205)</bibRefCitation>
and first suggested that the name 
<taxonomicName id="16AECEBCC369BA29FC42FC6085DFFC38" box="[973,1219,989,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Coccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ficus" subSpecies="caricae">
<emphasis id="E3DA692DC369BA29FC42FC6085DFFC38" box="[973,1219,989,1014]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Coccus ficus caricae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might possibly be the same as 
<taxonomicName id="16AECEBCC369BA29FEABFBBE8389FBD3" authority="Linnaeus. Current" authorityName="Linnaeus. Current" box="[292,661,1027,1053]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Coccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rusci">
<emphasis id="E3DA692DC369BA29FEABFBBE80A7FBD2" box="[292,443,1027,1052]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Coccus rusci</emphasis>
Linnaeus. Current
</taxonomicName>
status: Signoret (1869: 847) treated the name as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="16AECEBCC369BA29FF39FB948098FB8C" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[182,388,1065,1090]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rusci">
<emphasis id="E3DA692DC369BA29FF39FB948098FB8C" box="[182,388,1065,1090]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ceroplastes rusci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.).
</paragraph>
